15 WHEREAS, she left an indelible mark on the Georgia School Boards Association through
16 her involvement in the creation of the Georgia Vision Project, an educational framework for
17 boards that includes input from board members, superintendents, teachers, teaching colleges,
18 elected officials, parents, and students; and
19 WHEREAS, she has selflessly served the State of Georgia as the Executive Director of the
20 Atlanta BeltLine Partnership, Inc., Director of the Human Services Department in Fulton
21 County, Director of Fulton County's Office of Aging, and on Governor Deal's Education
22 Advisory Board; and
23 WHEREAS, Mrs. Wilson's significant organizational and leadership talents, remarkable
24 patience and diplomacy, keen sense of vision, and sensitivity to the needs of the citizens of
25 this state have earned her the respect and admiration of her colleagues and associates; and
26 WHEREAS, she is a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation for
27 integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness; and
28 WHEREAS, Mrs. Wilson has served with honor and distinction with the Georgia School
29 Boards Association, and her vision and unyielding commitment to excellence have set the
30 standard for public service; and
31 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
32 remarkable and distinguished Georgian be appropriately recognized.
33 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
34 recognize and commend Mrs. Valarie Wilson for her efficient, effective, unselfish, and
